# Docs harness

This repo follows the Harness Engineering principle for docs: the repo is the
system of record, and any change to code should update the doc(s) that own
those code paths in the same change. The 100-line `AGENTS.md` is the table of
contents; the chapters live in `docs/`.

When this rule is in scope, the `postToolUse` and `stop` hooks in
`.cursor/hooks.json` will run `scripts/docs-check.sh` to remind you. Trust the
reminder.

## Where to look

- Map: `AGENTS.md`
- Floor plan / file ownership: `ARCHITECTURE.md`
- Why-it's-like-this: `docs/design-docs/core-beliefs.md`
- Build, formatter, hooks: `docs/RELIABILITY.md`
- Per-feature behavior: `docs/product-specs/`
- In-flight plans: `docs/exec-plans/active/`

## Ownership map (must stay in sync with `ARCHITECTURE.md` and `code_to_docs` in `scripts/docs-check.sh`)

| You're touching… | Update… |
| --- | --- |
| `_layouts/default.html`, `_layouts/home.html` | `docs/product-specs/sidebar-navigation.md`, `docs/DESIGN.md` |
| `_layouts/post.html`, `_layouts/page.html`, `404.html` | `docs/product-specs/post-layout.md`, `docs/DESIGN.md` |
| Other `_layouts/`, `_includes/` | `docs/product-specs/index.md`, `docs/DESIGN.md` |
| `assets/css/style.scss` (or any `assets/` CSS/SCSS) | `docs/DESIGN.md` |
| `_posts/**`, `index.markdown`, `about.markdown`, other `*.markdown` | `docs/CONTENT.md` |
| `_config.yml`, `Gemfile`, `Gemfile.lock` | `docs/RELIABILITY.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md` |
| `.githooks/**`, `.prettierrc.json`, `.prettierignore` | `docs/RELIABILITY.md` |
| `.cursor/**`, `.codex/**`, `.claude/**`, `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `ARCHITECTURE.md`, `scripts/docs-check.sh` | `docs/design-docs/core-beliefs.md`, `docs/RELIABILITY.md` |

## Do

- Update the relevant doc(s) in the **same** edit that changes the code.
- For non-trivial work, open a plan under `docs/exec-plans/active/` first.
- Run `bash scripts/docs-check.sh --mode lint` before you stop.
- If you change the harness itself (this rule, the script, a hook config),
  update `docs/design-docs/core-beliefs.md` and `docs/RELIABILITY.md` together.

## Don't

- Don't grow `AGENTS.md` past 150 lines. The lint will fail.
- Don't disable the `postToolUse` or `stop` hook to silence the reminder. If
  the reminder is wrong, fix `code_to_docs` inside `scripts/docs-check.sh`.
- Don't add a doc that isn't reachable from `docs/README.md` or `AGENTS.md`.
- Don't bypass the pre-commit hook — see `.cursor/rules/commit-hook.mdc`.
